HR Portal Privacy Policy
Welcome to the HR Portal Privacy Policy! This document explains how we ("HR Portal," "we," "us," or "our") collect, use, share, and protect your personal information when you use our mobile application (the "App"). We are committed to safeguarding your privacy and ensuring that your data is handled securely and responsibly.

1. Information We Collect
To provide and improve our services, we collect various types of information from and about users of our App:

1.1 Personal Information
We collect essential personal information that allows you to access and use our services, including:

User ID
Password
1.2 Location Information
We collect your location information strictly for specific functionalities, like attendance tracking. Your location data is never used for any other purposes and is collected only with your explicit consent.

1.3 Usage Data
We gather information on how you interact with the App, such as:

Features accessed
Pages visited
Time spent on each feature or page
2. Information We Do Not Collect
We respect your privacy, so we do NOT collect:

Device type and model
Operating system version
Unique device identifiers (such as IMEI, MAC address)
IP address
3. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:

Provide and operate the App to ensure it functions correctly and deliver the services you request.
Process requests and transactions within the App.
Communicate with you about the App, updates, or changes relevant to your use or employment.
Personalize your experience based on your usage patterns and preferences.
Enhance security, prevent fraud, and ensure compliance with legal obligations.
4. Sharing Your Information
4.1 No Sale of Personal Information
We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third-party companies for their marketing or other purposes.

4.2 Third-Party Service Providers
We may share your information with third-party service providers who help us operate the App and provide services to you. These providers are obligated to protect your information and use it only for the purposes we specify.

4.3 Legal Requirements
We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or if we believe such action is necessary to:

Comply with legal obligations or respond to valid legal processes, such as subpoenas or court orders.
Protect and defend our rights or property.
Prevent or investigate possible wrongdoing in connection with the App.
Protect the safety of users or the public.
5. Your Choices
You have several options regarding your personal information:

You can access and update your personal information through the App's settings.
You can withdraw your consent for us to collect and process your location information at any time via the Appâ€™s settings.
If you no longer wish to use the App or have your information collected, you can uninstall the App from your device.
6. Security of Your Information
We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. Our security measures include encryption, access controls, and secure servers. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure. We strive to protect your personal information, but we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

7. Retention of Your Information
We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, including any legal, accounting, or reporting requirements. When your information is no longer required, we will securely delete or anonymize it in accordance with applicable laws and regulations.

8. Children's Privacy
Our App is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us at 90.tweenty.three@gmail.com. We will promptly delete such information from our records.

9. International Data Transfers
Your personal information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than the one in which you reside. These countries may have data protection laws that differ from the laws of your country. We ensure that any transfers of your personal information comply with applicable data protection laws and that your information remains protected.

10. Third-Party Integrations
Audio and Video Calls:
The App allows users to make audio and video calls through third-party platforms, such as Agora. While using these features, your information, such as audio and video data, may be processed by these third-party platforms according to their privacy policies. We recommend reviewing the privacy policies of any third-party service providers before using these features.

11. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on the App. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your information.

12. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at 90.tweenty.three@gmail.com.

13. Disclaimer
This Privacy Policy is provided for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal advice. We encourage you to consult with an attorney to ensure that your privacy policy fully complies with applicable laws and regulations.
